import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='population', y='engineers')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the number of engineers and the population of each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Engineers')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['engineers_per_capita'] = data['engineers'] / data['population']
    data = data.sort_values(by='engineers_per_capita', ascending=False)
    max_state = data.iloc[0]['state']
    max_value = data.iloc[0]['engineers_per_capita']

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='state', y='engineers_per_capita', data=data)
    ax.axhline(max_value, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {max_value:.2f}')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Engineers per Capita')
    plt.title('Which state has the highest number of engineers per capita?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='hurricanes', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['hurricanes'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['hurricanes'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Number of Hurricanes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of hurricanes that have affected each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='population', y='hurricanes', hue='state', legend='brief')
    plt.title('Is there a relationship between the number of hurricanes and the population of each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Hurricanes')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.2, 1), title='State')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['hurricanes_per_capita'] = data['hurricanes'] / data['population']
    data = data.sort_values(by='hurricanes_per_capita', ascending=False)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='state', y='hurricanes_per_capita', data=data)
    plt.title('Which state has the highest number of hurricanes per capita?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Hurricanes per Capita')
    
    max_hurricanes_per_capita = data['hurricanes_per_capita'].max()
    max_state = data.loc[data['hurricanes_per_capita'].idxmax(), 'state']
    plt.axhline(y=max_hurricanes_per_capita, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {max_state} ({max_hurricanes_per_capita:.2f})')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
